  "title": "Senior Physicist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>To do treatment planning for external beam radiotherapy and brachytherapy.</li>\n  <li>To discuss clinical cases with the consultant on treatment plans and techniques.</li>\n  <li>To perform output measurements, calibrations and quality assurance on relevant machine related to radiotherapy equipment periodically</li>\n  <li>To review daily QA procedure performed by Radiation Therapist</li>\n  <li>To supervise the radiation therapists to ensure that they perform their duties in accordance to the standards required of them and that they observe the radiation safety rules.</li>\n  <li>Assist in ensuring the PMIs of the radiotherapy equipment are done as per schedule and all test reports of equipment maintenance are reviewed</li>\n  <li>Assist in frontline troubleshooting for all therapy related machines and service engineer coordination</li>\n  <li>Assist in the MOH and NEA regulatory compliance Assist department quality/safety project(s).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Masters/Degree in Medical Physics (Radiation Therapy) or equivalent</li>\n  <li>Preferably with at least 5 years of relevant experience</li>\n</ul>",
